	<text>
		<body xml:lang="en">
			<div>

	<pb n="0001" facs="liv_001133_0001"/><!--pb/@n='85r'-->
<lb/><p rend="right"><placeName>Oxford</placeName>
<lb/>18<hi rend="sup"><hi rend="underline">th</hi></hi> Nov 
<lb/>1857</p>
<lb/><p>My Dear <persName>M<hi rend="sup"><hi rend="underline">r</hi></hi> Murray</persName></p>
<lb/><p>I enclose a 
<lb/>note to the granting 
<lb/>of which I see 
<lb/>no objection but 
<lb/>you must decide 
<lb/>and be kind 
<lb/>enough as to answer 
<lb/>it. </p>
<lb/><p>The meeting here 
<lb/>came off well 

	<pb n="0002" facs="liv_001133_0002"/><!--pb/@n='85v'--> 
<lb/>yesterday. I got 
<lb/>a good reception 
<lb/>in the Theatre &amp; 
<lb/>three cheers when 
<lb/>all was over<reg>,</reg>
<lb/>the young men 
<lb/>listened with 
<lb/>great attention 
<lb/>and no lecture 
<lb/>was ever so 
<lb/>well attended 
<lb/>by day as mine<reg>.</reg>
<lb/>I shall finish off 

	<pb n="0003" facs="liv_001133_0003"/><!--pb/@n='86r'--> 
<lb/>all by <placeName>Bradford</placeName>
<lb/>on <del type="strikethrough">Friday</del> Saturday 
<lb/>or Monday. &amp; then 
<lb/>farewell for ever 
<lb/>to public spouting 
<lb/>in favour of 
<lb/>"<persName>Murray</persName> &amp; <persName>Mudie</persName>"!! 
<lb/>What a ruffian 
<lb/>that fellow must 
<lb/>be whoever he is. 
<lb/>I hear <choice><sic>the</sic><corr>that</corr></choice> the copy 
<lb/>I sent to <persName>M<hi rend="sup">r</hi> Crawford</persName>
<lb/>has mollified him<reg>.</reg>
<lb/>He is favourable 

	<pb n="0004" facs="liv_001133_0004"/><!--pb/@n='86v'--> 
<lb/>in the "<choice><reg>E</reg><orig>e</orig></choice>xaminer" He 
<lb/>thanked me for it 
<lb/>at the meeting of 
<lb/>R.G.S. </p>
<lb/><p rend="center">I am &amp;c </p>
<lb/><p rend="center"><persName>D. Livingstone</persName></p>
<lb/><p>I went to Mayale &amp; 
<lb/>Polybank's on 
<lb/>Tuesday if you 
<lb/>need a new plate 
<lb/>that may do for it<reg>.</reg></p>
			
</div>
